        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 19 at 3:34PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 333 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Big Sandy, or 8 miles west of Gladewater, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gladewater, Big Sandy, Union Grove, Warren City, and Pritchett.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
